'''''Star Wars Insider'' 56''' is the fifty-sixth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[October 2]], [[2001]]. Issue 56 was the last produced by [[Christopher Perkins]], who had taken over as ''Star Wars Insider''{{'s}} chief editor with [[Star Wars Insider 55|issue 55]]. This issue featured a reverse flip cover on the back of the magazine with related content focusing on filmmaker [[Wikipedia:Kevin Smith|Kevin Smith]], known for his role in the character duo [[Wikipedia:Jay and Silent Bob|Jay and Silent Bob]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"Episode II [[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]"
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[Bookshelf]]" &mdash; [[Troy Denning|Troy and Troy]] Again {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Gamescape]]" &mdash; Take Your Seat on the Senate {{C|by [[Joe Alread]]}}
*"[[Set Piece]]: The Palace of Jabba the Hutt" {{C|by [[Chris Reiff]] & [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Help Celebrate a Scouting Anniversary! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Dear 2-1B]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[Behind the Episode I: The Phantom Menace DVD|Behind the Episode I: ''The Phantom Menace'' DVD]]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]], [[Ted A. Bohus]], and [[Terry Coleman]]}}
*:<small>New scenes. New special FX. New interviews. It's Episode I like you've never seen it before. What a glorious time to be a ''Star Wars'' fan!</small>
*"[[Jar Jar Binks Take 2: An Interview with Ahmed Best]]" {{C|by [[Helen Keier]]}}
*:<small>Kids love Jar Jar. Some adults hate Jar Jar. Now see what Ahmed Best thinks of Jar Jar and the direction the character is taking in Episode II.</small>
*"[[A Touch of Wry: Anthony Daniels on Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Brian J. Robb]]}}
*:<small>He's created a cultural icon and holds a degree in Human-Cyborg Relations. What more could Tony Daniels desire? How 'bout some nice bodywork for his good friend C-3PO?</small>
*"[[Unseen Planets of Episode I]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Take a tour of the worlds and wonders mentioned&mdash;but not explored&mdash;in ''The Phantom Menace''.</small>
*"Chasing Chewie: A Conversation with [[Kevin Smith]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Kevin Smith embraces his destiny, playing off his love of ''Star Wars'' in his latest film, ''Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back''.</small>

